The '''2008â09 Washington State Cougars men's basketball team''' represents [[Washington State University]] for the [[2008-09 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]]. The team plays its home games on Jack Friel Court in [[Beasley Coliseum]] in [[Pullman, WA|Pullman]], [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]].<ref>{{cite web|title= Washington State men's basketball|url=http://wsucougars.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/wast-m-baskbl-body.html|work=|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5hLPY5Lz9|archivedate=Jun. 6, 2009|deadurl=no|accessdate=Mar. 8, 2009}}</ref>
At the end of March 2009, [[Tony Bennett (basketball)|Tony Bennett]] announced that he was leaving [[Washington State Cougars men's basketball|Washington State]] to take the head coaching job at [[Virginia Cavaliers men's basketball|Virginia]].<ref>[http://sports.espn.go.com/ncb/news/story?id=4028642 Virginia to name Bennett coach]</ref> [[Ken Bone]], formerly with Portland State, takes over.
